jQuery Gaussian blur plugin

Blurs elements in a particular direction. To blur horizontally, for example, you can do this:

  $('selector').gaussian ({dx: 10, n: 10});

To achieve circular blurring you need to blur once horizontally and then blur vertically:

  $('selector').gaussian ({dx: 5, n: 5}).gaussian ({dy: 5, n: 5});

You can remove blurring from an element and restore the original by invoking gaussian(null):

  $('selector').gaussian (null);
